history.content:
4+ quick things:

1) 160 instructor flagged that he may need to change the schedule. Any schedule change will be confirmed by no later than this coming Monday (April 8). No, I don't know what the new schedule might be. You will find out (by looking at classes.berkeley.edu) some 

2) It is likely to be limited to 120 students (including 260A grads) for F19 so using phase 1 will be necessary and not necessarily sufficient to get in.

3) CS classes are all pre-approved for time conflicts. There is no form.

4) That being said, 160 will be unlikely to be webcast and much of lecture time --particularly but not exclusively-- later in the semester is used for hands-on group work which means you have to be able to not attend whatever class you have that might conflict with 160.

***

Also, there are a lot of questions re the schedule that basically say something to the effect of will something that is different than what it says on the schedule happen.  Staff won't be answering any of those because our best understanding of reality is what the schedule demonstrates.  Sure, some faculty free will decisions that we haven't yet been informed of may require changes but we are as limited in our mind-reading and oracle skills as the rest of you...
